      • setType

        public void setType(String type)
        Sets the xsi:type attribute for the element. Note that this basically adds a new attribute called "type" in the "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" namespace - it doesn't automatically declare this namespace with the "xsi" prefix. If the xsi prefix is declared with XMLNode.declarePrefix(String, String) method on this element or any higher elements, it this will come out as xsi:type.
        Specified by:
        setType in interface XMLNode
        Parameters:
        type - The type, as a string.
